04/04/2006
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- High Representative Christian Schwarz-Schilling and Republika Srpska (RS) Prime Minister Milorad Dodik agreed on the need for full co-operation with the UN war crimes tribunal, during a meeting in Banja Luka on Monday (3 April). 
Dodik says he assured Schwarz-Schilling of the new entity government's full determination to settle remaining obligations to the tribunal. 
During the talks, the High Representative also called for accelerated restructuring of the police.
Also on Monday, Schwarz-Schilling issued a decision partially reinstating officials discharged by his predecessors in BiH. 
The officials -- except for those removed for reasons related to co-operation with the UN war crimes tribunal -- would be allowed again to apply for and hold positions in public companies and public institutions.
In other news, Dutch European Affairs Minister Atzo Nicolai visited Sarajevo Monday for talks with BiH Prime Minister Adnan Terzic. 
He reaffirmed his country's support for the reform process and Euro-Atlantic aspirations. 
(PBS BiH, RTRS, Fena - 03/04/06)
